article.headline: North Florida 54, Stetson 44
article.story: DELAND, Fla. -- Brad Haugabrook scored 16 points and Jerron Granberry added 15, leading North Florida to a 54-44 win over Stetson on Sunday. Haugabrook made 7 of 12 shots from the floor, while Granberry connected on 5 of 8 shots and made all four of his free throws in a game which the Ospreys (8-8, 3-3 Atlantic Sun Conference) made only 16 of 26 attempts from the stripe. North Florida won for the seventh time in its past eight games. Stetson (3-11, 1-5) suffered its eighth loss in its past nine games. Stetson got a double-double from freshman forward Ridge Graham, who scored 15 points and grabbed 14 rebounds. A.J. Smith, Stetson's leading scorer for the season, had 10 points, but played just 3 minutes in the second half after spraining an ankle. Stetson got within 46-42 on a jumper by Graham with 2:36 to play, but North Florida scored six unanswered points to seal it.
